The paper deals with the problem of background subtraction in video inspection systems, which is a common task in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a computationally efficient method for background modeling, which involves solving a convex optimization problem using a low-rank matrix completion framework. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions the use of an extended Frank-Wolfe algorithm, which is a method commonly used in optimization and signal processing, suggesting that the paper could also be relevant to the category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
